.TH HEIC-TO-JPEG 1 "January 2026" "0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
heic-to-jpeg \- convert HEIC images to JPEG format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B heic-to-jpeg
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] <input files or directory>
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B heic-to-jpeg
converts HEIC (High Efficiency Image Container) images to JPEG format.
It supports batch conversion and parallel processing for efficient handling
of multiple files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-o \fI<path>\fR
Specify output directory for converted JPEG files.
Default: current directory.
.TP
.B \-v
Enable verbose logging to show detailed conversion progress.
.TP
.B \-q \fI<quality>\fR
Set JPEG quality level (1-100).
Higher values produce better quality but larger files.
Default: 100.
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a single HEIC file to JPEG in the current directory:
.PP
.nf
.RS
heic-to-jpeg photo.heic
.RE
.fi
.PP
Convert multiple HEIC files with custom quality:
.PP
.nf
.RS
heic-to-jpeg -q 85 photo1.heic photo2.HEIC
.RE
.fi
.PP
Convert with verbose output to specific directory:
.PP
.nf
.RS
heic-to-jpeg -v -o ./output photo.heic
.RE
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All conversions completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
One or more conversions failed.
